@hequn8128 
First, NULLIF(uuid(), uuid()) won't succeed to return null because of the "ReduceExpressionsRule", which will regard uuid() and uuid() as the same based on the "uuid()" string, it's the same for othere functions like current_timestamp.
Second, putting two uuid() into the same row may not test "isDeterministic" function. for example, we assume that the "isDeterministic" returns true: the outputs are different when the input is  "select uuid(),uuid() from testdata(1 row)", while the outputs are the same when the input is "select uuid() from testdata(2 rows)".

Seems correct, especially because the comment above that part indicates that the stream should not be closed.

